In addition to Tianhe District, Tao Tao Ju stores in Guangzhou's Baiyun District have been shut down by market regulators.

On February 20, Guangdong Province issued guidelines on the prevention and control of new pneumonia in the catering service industry to guide catering operators to gradually resume their canteen services during the epidemic period.

According to the working guidelines, Guangdong divided the prevention and control areas into counties (cities and districts) , and according to the current situation of the epidemic and its development trend, according to the number of newly reported cases in the last 14 days, the number of newly reported cases of local infection in the last 14 days, and whether the local outbreak happened in the last 14 days, there are four grades: Grade I, Grade II, Grade III and Grade IV.

No canteen service in Level II control area, but private room service is allowed. Level III prevention and control area to carry out restricted dining services, to promote the reduction of table and chair arrangement, table arrangement, dining staff into the catering business unit must take temperature, each table registration at least one dining guest's name and contact information.
